main event: A person spotted two unidentified flying objects (UFOs) over Garwood, New Jersey on December 31, 1969 around 1:00 AM.
interesting points: The observer reported that the objects were hovering and then suddenly accelerated out of sight.
The objects were described as being about 30 feet in diameter and white in color.
The objects were observed for about 10 minutes at an elevation of around 30 degrees above the horizon.
The observer had also reported sightings on October 30, 1967 and November 6, 1967, making this report considered 'unreliable'.
No photograph of the UFOs was provided with the report.
sighted object: two white, hovering objects that suddenly accelerated out of sight
